title: For Sale/Trade:  German (Bavarian) WW1 Sawback Bayonet
postcontent:
German (Bavarian) 1916 98/05 Butcher "Sawback" Bayonet (S98/05 nA S)

One of the best remembered German bayonets from the First World War, said to be inhumane due to the Saw teeth on the 14-inch blade. It was even said that German Soldiers captured with these Sawback bayonets were shot immediately. This was only a rumor, but many German soldiers removed the Saw teeth as a result. The Sawbacks were intended for Pioneer work like artillery emplacements and were never intended to mete out a gruesome death.

The truth is the British invented the saw back bayonet back in the middle of the 19th century.  My example is marked on the blade as being made by Fichtel & Sachs in Schweinfurt, which was made famous in WW2 as a target for our bombers.

I obtained this "evil babykiller" bayonet from an elderly neighbor who's father brought it home from "The Great War".  Made for use with the Gewehr 98 rifle, it's Bavarian (Crown over "L" for Ludwig III) and dated 1916 with a steel scabbard and working release button. The saw teeth are quite sharp, and there are no cracks in the grip panels, just some light rust on the scabbard and pommel. As can be seen in the photos, the blade has some staining but no active rust. I've cleaned up the blade a little with Flitz and a cotton cloth, but I didn't want to do too much to it as I was told that it might be blood staining. I then applied a couple coats of Eezox as a preservative. The edge was sharpened at some point in the past.

It was appraised at between $425 and $450, and a very similar bayonet is currently for sale on a popular militaria website for $395, but I'm making it available here for $350 cash in Northeast Florida. I'm also willing to consider trades for firearms of similar value FTF in NE FL. Just let me know what you have to trade! 

Serious inquiries only, please.

postcontent:
I have one NIB custom Savage Model 11 .243 with accu trigger and Bushnell 3x9x40 mm scope with flip caps. box, papers, lock, accu trigger tool, rifle sock and padded case with shoulder strap and ammo. I purchased this rifle for myself and customized it. It came with the factory composite stock and composite trigger guard. I restocked it in hardwood and free-floated the (factory contoured) barrel (completely to the action). It also has the savage "Chief" in brass set in the grip cap. Sling studs have been set. The action screws have been properly torqued. The trigger guard was replaced with a factory metal trigger guard to match the barrel and action. The bolt is jeweled and the barrel is luster blued (not the terrible finishes you see these days!). It also comes with a Bushnell 3x9x40 scope (with flip caps) that I have bore sighted for 100 yards (it will still need final sighting in). It also comes with a leather Savage sling with quick detach sling rings. It also includes a rifle sock for protection, a padded rifle case with shoulder strap and accessory pouch. Also, included is the original composite stock, a metal trigger guard to work with the composite stock if you wish. It also comes with the original composite trigger guard. Last, it comes with 120 rounds of ammunition (new, not reloads!). 3 boxes of Winchester 100 GR Power Point, 2 boxes of Federal 100 GR Soft Point and 1 box of Remington 80 GR PSP. The rifle alone cost 644.99. The sling cost 45.00, padded case, 43.00, sock 9.99, stock 150.00, trigger guard for wood stock 25.00, trigger guard for composite stock 23.00, flip caps 40.00, the ammo 171.00, etc. The custom work I did on this rifle I normally charge 300.00. 

I have over 1,411.00 invested with my labor. Originally I bought this rifle as a custom build for myself as a Varmint rifle. However, with bills to pay I need to sell it. It is new, not fired, not carried, etc. All accessories are new! ...Everything is absolutely new, so please do not ask.

The custom work is not cheap as anyone who has had custom work done knows (...and I do not do cheap work). This is a great deal for someone. It will not last long. My loss is definitely someone's gain! 

Note: This is a regular size adult stock, not a youth. The .243 was never created to be a youth cartridge (even though many use it as one). It was created to be an intermediate cartridge both for deer, varmint and black bear (which it does work!).

The rifle’s tubular magazine can pack ten powerful .45 bruisers. Made in USA.
